@@ Canonical Plugin Structure

Each plugin MUST follow this structure:

```
plugins/<plugin-name>/
├── src/
│   └── <plugin_package>/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── plugin.py
│       ├── manifest.json
│       ├── inference/
│       ├── utils/
│       └── configs/
├── tests_contract/
├── tests_heavy/
├── pyproject.toml
├── README.md
└── Makefile
```

FORBIDDEN STRUCTURES (will be caught by pre-commit hook):
- plugins/<plugin-name>/<plugin_package>/ (source at root, not in src/)
- plugins/<plugin-name>/<plugin_package>/<plugin_package>/ (duplicate nesting)
- plugins/src/ (src at plugins root, not per-plugin)

This ensures:
✓ One canonical module root per plugin
✓ Consistent import paths across all plugins
✓ No duplicate module resolution conflicts
